## Role-based work boundaries

This is a 4-person team. Each contributor owns ONE layer of the system.

ALWAYS check for a file named `my-role.md` in the repo root. If it exists,
read it BEFORE generating code and respect the boundaries it defines.

If `my-role.md` does not exist, ASK the user which persona they are
(Persona 1, 2, 3, or 4) before generating code that touches multiple layers.

Layer ownership:
- Persona 1: /backend/data + /backend/main.py + Supabase schemas
- Persona 2: /backend/agents (Crystal Ball, Expansion, Closed-Loop)
- Persona 3: /backend/automations (Make, ElevenLabs, channel routing)
- Persona 4: /frontend (React, dashboard, demo views)

Cross-layer changes require updating CONTRACTS.md first.

This project follows strict contracts defined in CONTRACTS.md.

ALWAYS:
- Read plan.md and CONTRACTS.md before generating code
- Use exact schema names, field names, and types from CONTRACTS.md
- Use snake_case in Python and JSON keys (per CONTRACTS.md section 6)
- Use camelCase only in TypeScript variables
- Generate UUIDs via uuid_generate_v4() in SQL, never as integers
- Reference endpoint URLs exactly as defined in CONTRACTS.md section 2

NEVER:
- Invent new database tables without updating CONTRACTS.md first
- Change endpoint signatures without team discussion
- Use mock data when real Supabase data is available
- Skip the playbook_id_used field in interventions table


## Project-specific rules

- All API endpoints live under /api/v1 prefix
- All timestamps are TIMESTAMPTZ in UTC
- All FastAPI endpoints must validate input via Pydantic models
- Frontend API client must convert snake_case → camelCase at the boundary
- Never call the LLM directly from the frontend; always go through FastAPI
- Voice audio is generated by ElevenLabs in FastAPI BEFORE Make is called,
  not inside the Make workflow
- Errors follow the format: {"error": "code", "message": "human readable", "details": {}}

## File placement
- Python agents go in /backend/agents/
- FastAPI routes go in /backend/routes/
- Make webhook handlers go in /backend/automations/
- React pages in /frontend/src/pages/
- Shared TypeScript types in /frontend/src/types/

## Git
- Branches: persona-N/feature-name (kebab-case)
- Commits: conventional (feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:)
- Never commit directly to main

When in doubt, ask the user. Do not assume.